# Group Policy Wallpaper Deployment Lab

## Objective

Deploy a company wallpaper to users in a specific Organizational Unit (OU) using Group Policy Objects (GPO).

## Lab Environment

- Windows Server 2022 Domain Controller
- Windows 10 Client
- VMware Workstation
- Active Directory Domain Services
- Group Policy Management

Domain:

charlycyber.local

## Tasks Performed

### 1. Created Organizational Units

The following OUs were created:

- HR
- FINANCE
- ITGUYS

### 2. Created Domain Users

Users were created and placed inside their respective OUs.

Example:

- HRuser1 (HR OU)

### 3. Created a Wallpaper GPO

A Group Policy Object named:

wallpaper policy

was created and linked to the HR OU.

### 4. Configured Wallpaper Policy

Path:

User Configuration → Policies → Administrative Templates → Desktop → Desktop → Desktop Wallpaper

Configuration:

- Enabled
- Wallpaper Style: Fill

Initial wallpaper path:

C:\Windows\Web\Wallpaper\Windows\img0.jpg

### 5. Verified Policy Application

Commands used:

gpupdate /force

gpresult /r

Results confirmed that the wallpaper policy was successfully applied to users in the HR OU.

### 6. Tested Network Share Deployment

A shared folder named wallpapers was created on the Domain Controller.

Shared path:

\192.168.134.10\wallpapers

The wallpaper file:

img0.jpg

was stored in the shared folder.

Connectivity was verified using:

dir \192.168.134.10\wallpapers

### 7. Troubleshooting

Issue:

Hostname-based share access failed.

Example:

\WIN-200J89MC3AS\wallpapers

Resolution:

Used the server IP address while investigating DNS/name-resolution issues.

## Skills Demonstrated

- Active Directory Administration
- Organizational Unit Management
- User Management
- Group Policy Administration
- Network Share Configuration
- Windows Troubleshooting
- DNS Troubleshooting
- User Policy Deployment

## Outcome

Successfully deployed a desktop wallpaper to users within the HR OU through Group Policy and validated access to a centralized network share.

